deck: Terri is the girl who help to Clark Kent to discover his powers and to understand to himself. She never felt fear with the Superman's powers.
description:
Overview

Clark Kent is confronted by Terri Chun in a coffe shop in Paris, she has taken few pictures of Clark Kent lifting a car in the scene of an accident. Clark used his powers and destroy the film. Then they had coffee and unbeknown to her. Hours later, she offered a place to stay to Clark and when they where at her place, suddenly they were attacked by few Chinese commandos. Seeing bullets simply bounce off Clark’s body, leads them to believe there is something wrong with their ammunition and they retreat. When asked Terri explains Chinese commando attacked them because her father is the Rhana Bhutra, highest religious figure in their country, and that the commandos intended to kidnap her to get to him.

After the brief conversation Clark and Terri charter a plane to fly to Terri´s home, when they are attacked mid-air. The plane explodes killing the pilot but Terri is saved by Clark who flies her home. They cross with Bruce Wayne on their way. Clark is then introduced to Terri’s father and Clark expresses his desire to live in Terri’s palace for a while to learn their culture and philosophy. The father humbly accepts. The next morning Clark and Terri’s father have a brief discussion about Clark’s superhuman powers and the conversation is interrupted when Clark flies away to save Terri from an avalanche. Terri after being saved kisses Clark and they fall in love.

Clark is thinking and meditating when sees that the chinese army is coming to the town in front of the terri´s palace, in Bhutan. Clark looks for Terri and then flies her to a desert where both see Terri’s father being killed by the Chinese Armies. This angers Clark who in turn attacks the armies in super speed, armies on the other hand believing it was the wrath of the god for killing Rhana Bhutra retreat. The death of her father now makes Terri the Rhana Bhutra. However being the Rhana Bhutra would mean, she has duty with her people and can be together with Clark no longer, Clark bids goodbye with a sad heart, we clearly see tears in his eyes just after Terri whispers “Your secrets will be safe with me”.
name: Terri Chun

deck: The highest religious figure in their country, BhutanHistory.
description:
History

The Rhana Bhutra is the religious leader who helped to Bruce Wayne and Clark Kent to find their Path. The Rhana Bhutra is killed by the chinese army because he is spreading a philosophy against China and the communism. When he died, Terri Chun, his daughter takes the position of Rhana Bhutra.
name: Rhana Bhutra

name: Ajahn

deck: Karla Faye Gideon's son was murdered, which led to her meeting Matt Murdock during the murder trial. When they first met she was loyal and defensive to her abusive husband, but years later was saved from her husband by Daredevil.
description:
Karla Faye was contacted by Matthew Murdock to ask about her murdered son Bradley. She was beaten by her husband but remained loyal to him, and even accused Daredevil of beating her husband.

Years later she needed to be saved by Daredevil from the husband she defended.

Karla Faye appeared in Episode 13 of the 2nd season of Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. She was portrayed by Drea de Matteo. Her character differs from her comics incarnation in that she had no ties to Daredevil and was an "enhanced" individual with razors grafted to her fingertips. She was defeated in combat by Bobbi Morse.
name: Karla Faye Gideon
